※※
# catalog-sky-library

Manually-run workflow that regenerates a browsable `INDEX.md` for a `.sky` directory —
one row per workflow (name, trigger, vars, node-DAG sketch, budget) — then verifies in
bash that every workflow is listed. One cheap Claude (haiku) node does the formatting;
the rest is bash. Re-run any time to refresh the map of your library.

  (manual run: --var dir)
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  count *.sky in <dir>
   │  scan  │
   └────────┘
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  haiku reads each .sky -> writes <dir>/INDEX.md table
   │ index  │  (sky-workflow-authoring skill)
   └────────┘
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  assert INDEX.md non-empty + every .sky listed
   │ verify │  exit 1 if any workflow is missing
   └────────┘

Run it (state which directory to catalog with --var dir):

  sky run catalog-sky-library --var dir=".sky/workflows"

  - dir   directory of .sky files to index — STATE THIS (e.g. .sky/workflows)

Install the skill it formats with (once):

  sky library install sky-workflow-authoring
※※

⊕meta⊕
name = "catalog-sky-library"
description = "Regenerate a browsable INDEX.md for a .sky directory (name, trigger, vars, DAG, budget) with a bash coverage check that every file is listed. Fire via: sky run catalog-sky-library --var dir=<path>"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
max_budget_usd = 1.00
⊕⊕

※scan※
Entry point: counts *.sky in {{dir}}. No dependencies. Stops cleanly if empty.
※※

§scan§
bash_file = "./scripts/scan.sh"
§§

※index※
Depends on scan. Haiku reads each .sky in {{dir}} and writes {{dir}}/INDEX.md table. Skills: sky-workflow-authoring.
※※

§index§
model = "haiku"
depends_on = ["scan"]
skills = ["sky-workflow-authoring"]
§§

∆index∆
List every `*.sky` file in {{dir}} (ignore INDEX.md and any non-.sky file). Read each one and extract: its `name` (from the ⊕meta⊕ block), its trigger type (manual / sky_event / github / cron), the `--var` inputs it expects, a one-line node-DAG sketch (node ids joined by `->` following depends_on edges), and `max_budget_usd` if set.

Write a Markdown file at {{dir}}/INDEX.md containing a `# Workflow Index` title, a one-line intro, and a table with the header `| Workflow | Trigger | Vars | Flow | Budget |`. One row per workflow, sorted by name; use `—` for an empty cell. Do not modify any `.sky` file. Output the path you wrote when done.
∆∆

※verify※
Depends on index. Bash coverage check: INDEX.md must exist, be non-empty, and list every .sky. Fails if stale.
※※

§verify§
depends_on = ["index"]
bash_file = "./scripts/verify.sh"
§§
